Package: alfak2
Title: Compiled Hierarchical Fitness Inference for Aneuploid Karyotypes
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Richard", family = "Beck",
           email = "richard.beck@moffitt.org", role = "aut"),
    person(given = "Tao", family = "Li",
           email = "Tao.Li2@moffitt.org", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Author: Richard Beck [aut], Tao Li [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Tao Li <Tao.Li2@moffitt.org>
Description: A compiled-first inference pipeline for sparse two-timepoint
    karyotype count data. The package fits a local hierarchical Bayesian
    posterior with TMB, then uses a graph Gaussian-process and ordered
    copy-number epistasis prior solved with RcppEigen sparse linear algebra.
